    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1866-02-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1866-02-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="729" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d729">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Bigelow</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Seward</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 272.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United
                                            States</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Paris</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1866-02-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">February</hi> 15, 1866.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I learn from an unofficial source that
                                Gregorio Barandiran, the diplomatic representative of the Archduke
                                Maximilian at Vienna, formerly secretary of legation under Señor
                                Robles at Washington, is now at Paris, for money to fit out 10,000
                                Austrians, which, he says, are ready to embark from Trieste for
                                Mexico. The Mexican commissioner informed him that there was no
                                money in his hands. I am not sure of learning the result of the
                                minister’s suit here, as the money, if furnished, must come through
                                indirect and concealed channels.</p>
                <p rend="center">* * * * * * * *</p>
                <p>I am, sir, with great respect, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>JOHN BIGELOW.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State, &amp;c., &amp;c.,
                                        &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
